      "index": 0,
      "title": "Seated Leg Curl (Machine)",
      "notes": "Sets: 2 Working Sets (Cut from 3 to save systemic energy).\n\nTarget: 10-12 reps @ RPE 10.\n\nRest: 2m 0s (Increased from 1m 30s to ensure total failure).\n\nPrimer: Wakes hamstrings. Acts as a \"protective sleeve\" for knees before heavy compounds.\n\nTempo: 3-second eccentric return.\n\nToe Position: Point toes toward shins (dorsiflexion) to lock the calf muscle and isolate the hamstring.\n\nPosture: Press lower back firmly into the seat; do not let the hips slide forward.",
