    {
      "index": 1,
      "title": "Hip Thrust (Machine)",
      "notes": "Base resistance: 22.7kg\n\nSets: 3 Working Sets + 1 Drop Set (Cut from 5 sets to prevent CNS crash).\n\nTarget: 8-12 reps @ RPE 10.\n\nRest: 3m 0s\n\nExecution:\n\nMass Builder: Maximizes glute contraction.\n\nThe Overload: Integrate the 3-second isometric hold at the top of the final reps, transitioning directly into lengthened partials for the drop set.\n\nPelvic Tuck: Ribs down; belly button to spine. Avoid hyperextending the lower back.\n\nStability: Dig heels into the plate. Slightly wider-than-shoulder-width stance. Toes pointed out 15–30°.",
