    {
      "index": 2,
      "title": "Romanian Deadlift (Dumbbell)",
      "notes": "Sets: 3 Working Sets.\n\nTarget: 6-10 reps @ RPE 10 (Increased rep range slightly to maximize Time Under Tension over raw force).\n\nRest: 3m 0s (Increased from 2m 0s).\n\nTempo: 3-second eccentric stretch. This is the primary growth driver.\n\nStretch Bias: Lengthens glutes under load. DBs provide a neutral center of gravity.\n\nSoft Knees: Maintain a micro-bend. Stop at mid-shin. Avoid knee hyperextension.\n\nSetup: Rotate palms slightly toward thighs to set shoulders and prevent the internal rotation caused by barbells.",
